  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, flour, piccalilli, and bake. Mix well.",
    "Pour in melted butter and mix until combined.",
    "Add beaten eggs and mix until a dough forms.",
    "Transfer the dough to a greased 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "Bake for 35-40 minutes or until the top is golden brown.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes.",
    "Cut into squares and serve warm."
